The paper deals with improving the performance of benchmark classifiers through preprocessing of time series data. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data science, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG and cs.DS. The use of smoothing algorithms also involves signal processing, which is covered by cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of domain knowledge in specific classification problems, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of time series data, which is covered by cs.IR.
